<p>If the psych wasn't there, then it wasn't a legal meeting. (If the v.p. wasn't there - but signed it - then technically it's legal because signing it means he's saying he was there.)  Looks like it's time for some damage control:  patching things up with the psych or learning to work over &amp;amp; around.  It stinks when the students get caught in the middle!</p>
